    "Specifically, the number of non-trigger word (\"O\" tags) exceeds another tag.",
    "When calculating the loss, the loss of the non-trigger word (\"O\" category) accounts for the majority of total losses, preventing the model from being effectively trained with the loss.",
    "For example, this issue is visually reflected in Fig. 1, despite the relatively short sentence length.",
    "Therefore, the current research encounters two main challenges.",
    "Firstly, the generation of discriminative prototypes is hindered by the limited availability of training data per batch."
